  steps:
  - title: 'Walkthrough Mode: Understanding Cost and Efficiency in SPRS'
    voText: In this walkthrough mode, you will be guided step by step through the
      calculations used to determine handling time, handling cost, and storage cost
      in a Single Pallet Racking System. These calculations form the baseline for
      understanding warehouse efficiency and will later be used in the experiment
      mode.
    assignedVoiceId: 
    generatedAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 370d873917ecf4a02bc8705bcad6f16b, type: 3}
    isDirty: 0
    lastGeneratedTime: 1/27/2026 1:14:47 AM
  - title: Base Cost Components of a Warehouse Using SPRS
    voText: The base cost of a warehouse using Single Pallet Racking System is the
      total cost incurred to store and handle pallets under normal operating conditions.
      This base cost is composed of rack cost, floor space cost, and handling cost.
    assignedVoiceId: 
    generatedAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 14ca64bf52cba4f0fb994b047e196221, type: 3}
    isDirty: 0
    lastGeneratedTime: 1/26/2026 7:31:07 PM
  - title: Understanding Floor Space Cost
    voText: Floor space cost refers to the cost associated with the physical area
      occupied by the warehouse. In SPRS, aisle width and rack layout are fixed,
      and therefore the floor space cost remains constant throughout this experiment.
    assignedVoiceId: 
    generatedAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 6681816dff1d94872b450292e961e8de, type: 3}
    isDirty: 0
    lastGeneratedTime: 1/26/2026 7:31:12 PM
  - title: Handling Cost in SPRS
    voText: Handling cost is the cost incurred while moving pallets inside the warehouse.
      It includes the cost of labor, equipment operation, energy consumption, and
      maintenance. In SPRS, handling cost is the most significant variable cost and
      the key factor influencing overall efficiency.
    assignedVoiceId: 
    generatedAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 665b1d26468404a659b65f889781ffb5, type: 3}
    isDirty: 0
    lastGeneratedTime: 1/26/2026 7:31:16 PM
  - title: Handling Time Breakdown for a Single Task
    voText: The handling time for a single task is the total time required to locate,
      move, lift, and place a pallet. In engineering terms, handling time is composed
      of search time, movement time, and lift time.
    assignedVoiceId: 
    generatedAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 1e684295d30f742ba8a06bf7231e6ea2, type: 3}
    isDirty: 0
    lastGeneratedTime: 1/26/2026 7:31:21 PM
  - title: Effect of Storage Strategy on Search and Movement Time
    voText: In a fixed storage strategy, each SKU has a predefined location. This
      reduces search time because the operator knows exactly where the pallet is
      stored. However, movement time may increase because space cannot be dynamically
      optimized. In a float storage strategy, pallets are stored in any available
      location. This reduces movement time by minimizing travel distance but increases
      search time, as the operator must identify the pallet location before retrieval.
    assignedVoiceId: 
    generatedAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 75c35760e05e14dec87529b9ea4df281, type: 3}
    isDirty: 0
    lastGeneratedTime: 1/26/2026 7:31:28 PM
  - title: Understanding Number of Tasks
    voText: The number of tasks represents the total number of pallet handling operations
      performed within a defined time period. Each task may involve storing a pallet,
      retrieving a pallet, or repositioning a pallet inside the warehouse.
    assignedVoiceId: 
    generatedAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 56b9696b844e04f01a7138f941747a73, type: 3}
    isDirty: 0
    lastGeneratedTime: 1/26/2026 7:31:33 PM
  - title: From Handling Time to Handling Cost
    voText: Handling cost is calculated by multiplying the total handling time by
      the cost of operating labor and equipment per unit time.
    assignedVoiceId: 
    generatedAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: d446518efe88a4e3c8166c72506c75de, type: 3}
    isDirty: 0
    lastGeneratedTime: 1/26/2026 7:31:36 PM
  - title: Storage Cost per Pallet in SPRS
    voText: The storage cost per pallet represents how much it costs to store and
      handle a single pallet in the warehouse. This value is used to compare efficiency
      across different operational choices.
    assignedVoiceId: 
    generatedAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: ad0d6ed3af21141989fa144110992440, type: 3}
    isDirty: 0
    lastGeneratedTime: 1/26/2026 7:31:39 PM
  - title: Applying the Knowledge in Experiment Mode
    voText: You have now understood how handling time, number of tasks, and storage
      strategy influence handling cost and overall efficiency in a Single Pallet
      Racking System. In the experiment mode, you will apply this knowledge by adjusting
      operational parameters to achieve the target efficiency.
    assignedVoiceId: 
    generatedAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: aa99c1ad9df4e48098f7d24f972e480b, type: 3}
    isDirty: 0
    lastGeneratedTime: 1/26/2026 7:31:44 PM
